title: For Sale:  EAA Baikal IZH-35M .22LR Russian Target Pistol w/Ultradot Matchdot II & 2 Mags
postcontent:
Up for sale is a IZH-35M target pistol. Picked it up as an impulse buy at a show and really don't have the time or motivation to learn to compete in NRA Conventional Pistol. I've put in around 200 rounds and have attached pictures of a couple of targets. (5 shot was 25 yds from a sandbag rest and 10 shot was 25 yds standing, off-hand). Both targets were using cheap Remington Standard Velocity and not match ammo. From a machine rest, I have no doubts there would be a single hole from 25yds. Judging from the brass deflector after shooting it once, this gun may have not been fired by the previous owner - though I couldn't guarantee that. 

Since purchasing it, I have cleaned it thoroughly with gun scrubber, blown it clean, and lightly oiled contact surfaces and pins. These guns were left quite rough from the factory and it was clear that it had never had the manufacturing debris cleaned out. Following the factory manual (as well as the Walther KSP200 manual), I have also set the trigger release and over-travel. Pull weight set around 2.5-3.0 lbs with Lyman digital gauge. I have also replaced the shroud screws with allen-headed screws - which is something almost all owners do as the factory screws are too soft, and loosen after just a few shots. I have also installed a factory rail (nearly impossible to source) and sourced a second magazine. The second magazine has NOT been fitted or used, and there is information online (http://www.ammoclip.com/images/IZH35M%20fitting%20instructions.pdf) indicating slight hand fitting is required. 

Pistol includes 2 (5-shot) magazines, installed rail, Ultradot Matchdot II red-dot sight (with all original box/papers/accessories), and a hard case. Asking price is $1250 OBO - completely open to offers. Only trades I'm really looking for at the moment are: 

-H&K 45C Tactical V3 .45ACP Pistol (not USP) 
-H&K Mk23 .45ACP Pistol 
-Ruger New Vaquero 5.5" Stainless .45LC Revolver

title: For Sale:  AK 74 5.45 x 39 Galil Style + Extras
postcontent:
For sale is a Romanian WASR-2 chambered in 5.45 x 39. $550 OBO.

This rifle has been modified from it's original ban-produced form. It features a Tapco G2 Trigger Group, Tapco Folding Galil Stock, Tapco Galil Handguard, and Tapco SAW Pistol Grip. The bolt carrier has been polished, and the mag well has been expanded to accept hi-cap magazines. The rifle comes with x1 30 round ProMag Magazine, and x2 10 round steel magazines. I am also including an extra Galil Handguard and SAW grip. This rifle is 100% 922r compliant.

The rifle is in good condition and has a round count of about 250. The trigger group was replaced after 160 rounds. There is some scuffing on the bottom of the receiver near the mag well as a result of the cutting process. The rifle is a WASR, and like most WASR's produced during the ban, it tends to jam from time to time. Usually just a  FTF that can be cleared by simply racking the gun. It likes to eat Mil-Surp ammo which is always available, even during scares.

If you haven't tried an AK-74 before, now is the time. The ammunition is about half the cost of .223/5.56, yet shares similar, if not better ballistics. The 5.45 round is potent, and earned the name 'Poison Bullet' in Afghanistan for it's wounding capabilities. Light recoil, hard hitting, and cheap!
